author: @ramadhaniainun
text:
FYI,  Daegari/Daegaree (대가리) means 'head' in Korean but it's kinda harsh. Chenle named his dog 'Daegal' (대갈).  In Korean, if the last letter in a name is a conjunction—in this case, DaegaL with the letter 'L' in the end, you have to add 'Ee' (이) to call her. So it will be 'DaegaLee'. And actually 'DaegaLee' is have to be pronounced like 'Daegaree'.
Hope this can helps you!
